<a href="javascript:card_browser(135)">Desperate Defense of the Ring</a> x4<br>
Enduring Evil x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(138)">Forces of Mordor</a> x3<br>
<br>
<br>
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> For the start, you almost always bid zero.<br>
You want your opponent to go first, so you can play on your own sites... <br>
<br>
Does not matter, if he starts Prancing Pony or not; if he does, you get your Aragorn for just one burden, while he will usually have up to five.<br>
<br>
That is where Enduring Evil really shines...With that strategy of your opponent you can end the game real quick.<br>
<br>
Should he start a different site one, no problem either, then it just takes a while longer to corrupt/ kil Frodo with Enduring Evil, but he wont have access to one of his most powerful characters for long.<br>
<br>
I play Prancing Pony as my starting site, in case my opponent bids high and lets me go first.<br>
<br>
The starting sites were selected to give out as few twilight as possible, Balins Tomb is a must, cosz its the only real &quot;neutral&quot; site at -4-, and the rest is all about forests/rivers for A Rangers Versatility, topped with Summit of Amon Hen for extra cards to end the game, should he prevail till then....<br>
<br>
For your fellowship, you have your basic Rangers, complete with Archery skills; Sam is only in there to remove burdens against a similar deck, other than that he can function as a bait for the Cave Troll, saving Frodo in the process....<br>
<br>
The small fellowship, combined with No Stranger to Shadows and Sting, means that you give out few twilight. You should almost always move to site three in one turn. Then according to the following pattern : 3-4, 4-5, 5-7, 7-8, 8-9 .<br>
<br>
Of course, you may have to double-move, in order not to lose the game by staying too much behind.<br>
<br>
After you are clear of the bridge, you can use A Rangers Versatility, Valliant Man of the West and PATHS to clear the way. <br>
<br>
Of course, this is just hypothetical, i have yet to test this deck - any suggestions are welcome!<br>
<br>
Thanks !!!<br>
<br>
Alex - RoR </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20332"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20332" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
